
@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam classAttributeIconColor #000000
skinparam classOperationIconColor #000000

class Person {
    +String firstName
    +String familyName
    +Date birthDate
}

class Trainer {
    +String diploma
}

class Member {
    // Inherited from Person
}

class Center {
    +String name
    +String address
    +List<Room> rooms
}

class Room {
    +int roomNumber
    +int maxCapacity
    +Center center
}

class Session {
    +Date date
    +Time startTime
    +Center center
    +Room room
    +Person participant
    +Trainer supervisor
}

class GroupSession {
    +String type
}

class IndividualSession {
    // No supervisor
}

class Prospect {
    // Not yet registered as a member or trainer
}

class Intern {
    // Not yet supervised any session
}

' Relationships
Person <|-- Member
Person <|-- Trainer
Trainer <|-- Intern
Member <|-- Prospect

Center "1" *-- "0..*" Room
Room "1" --> "1" Center

Session "1" *-- "1" Center
Session "1" *-- "1" Room
Session "1" *-- "1" Person
Session "0..1" *-- "1" Trainer

GroupSession <|-- Session
IndividualSession <|-- Session

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements in the Diagram:

- **`Person`**: Base class with attributes `firstName`, `familyName`, and `birthDate`.
- **`Trainer`** and **`Member`**: Subclasses of `Person`. A person can be both a `Trainer` and a `Member`.
- **`Prospect`** and **`Intern`**: Represent people who are not yet members or trainers but may become one.
- **`Center`**: Has a name, address, and multiple rooms.
- **`Room`**: Belongs to a center and has a number and capacity.
- **`Session`**: Abstract class with fields for date, start time, center, room, participant, and optional supervisor.
- **`GroupSession`** and **`IndividualSession`**: Subclasses of `Session`. Only `GroupSession` requires a `Trainer` as a supervisor.
- **Multiplicity constraints**:
  - A `Center` can have many `Rooms`.
  - A `Room` belongs to exactly one `Center`.
  - A `Session` must belong to one `Center` and one `Room`.
  - A `Session` is attended by exactly one `Person`.
  - A `GroupSession` is supervised by exactly one `Trainer`.

